        "summary":  "Anthropic developed the Jacobian lens (J-lens), a tool that reveals a hidden reasoning layer called J-space inside Claude Opus 4.6, exposing the words the model considers before generating responses. The findings show that LLMs perform complex reasoning in ways that differ from their visible explanations, revealing problem-solving steps not explicitly stated in outputs.",
